

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="About | Adrianne Codes">
  <div class="site-shell">
    <aside class="site-sidebar">
      <Nav />
    </aside>

    <main class="site-main">
      <section class="about-page content-shell content-shell--white content-shell--reading">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>Hi, I’m Adrianne.</h1>

        <p>
          I’m a curious builder who likes turning experiments, notes, and messy ideas into clear,
          useful things. Adrianne Codes is my space for frontend projects, technical writing,
          tutorials, and learning in public.
        </p>

        <h2>What this site is</h2>
        <p>
          This site is part portfolio, part technical notebook. I use it to document what I build,
          what I’m learning, and how I think through the process — especially when it comes to
          frontend development, content systems, and writing that helps other people follow along.
        </p>

        <h2>My site ecosystem</h2>
        <p>
          I split my work across a few focused spaces so each one can stay clear and intentional:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Adrianne Codes</strong> — frontend projects, tutorials, and technical writing</li>
          <li><strong>Prompted by Adrianne</strong> — AI experiments and prompt case studies</li>
          <li><strong>Patterned by Adrianne</strong> — data projects, dashboards, and analysis</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          This setup lets me separate early ideas and learning notes from more polished work.
        </p>

        <h2>A quick history</h2>
        <p>
          I’ve been building websites for a long time, starting from the early days of the web:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>c. 1997–1998</strong> — A Dragon Ball Z fanfiction site hosted on the now-defunct GeoCities
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>2001</strong> — <em>balamb-epitaph.net</em>, a Final Fantasy VIII fan collective and my first site with its own domain
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>2002</strong> — <em>funyaraga.nu</em>, a personal site experimenting with design, fandom, and “random whatevers” during the early indie web era
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          This current site is part of a much longer journey — just built with better tools, clearer thinking, and a lot more experience.
        </p>

        <h2>What I care about</h2>
        <p>
          I care about clarity, accessibility, and thoughtful design. I’m especially interested in
          the intersection of frontend work, technical writing, data, and ethical AI — not just how
          tools work, but how people actually use them.
        </p>

        <h2>Credentials</h2>
        <p>
          My certifications and credentials live on
          <a href="https://adrianne.io/credentials" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Portal by Adrianne
          </a>.
          This site focuses on the work, the writing, and the learning behind it.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .about-page ul {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .about-page li {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .about-page p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>